To do development on code in this subdir tree,

check out this tree from svn
Add the following to the bottom of your ~/.my_defaults file:

  ################################################################################
  # Insert script setup command
  ################################################################################
  setenv SCRIPTS_DIR /net/work/bin/scripts/insert/
  setenv MYSQL_DIR /net/work/lib/perl/mysql/

where you replace the paths with the path to where you checked out these
scripts. If you are also doing development on the mysql libraries, check them
out and change the above path

> source ~/.my_defaults
> printenv 
	- to confirm the above two env vars have been added

To deploy your changes, go to the production area and check out the code.

To go back to production

comment out lines in .my_defaults by putting a # at the beginning of the line
unsetenv SCRIPTS_DIR
